  <body>
    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1">CLEAR MEMORY Command</para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="NotesBox"><snippet src="__NotInCoreVulcan" inline="false"/></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><snippet src="__CommandInclude" inline="false"/></para>
    <para styleclass="Heading1">Purpose</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal">Deletes both public and private memory variables from the memory variable table.</para>
    <para styleclass="Heading1">Syntax</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal">CLEAR MEMORY</para>
    <para styleclass="Heading1">Description</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal">This command operates in contrast to RELEASE ALL, which does not actually delete public and private memory variables but assigns NIL to those with scope limited to the current procedure. CLEAR MEMORY is the only way to delete all public memory variables from current memory. Declared variables and constants, however, are unaffected by CLEAR MEMORY.</para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text"><snippet src="__IncludeLibRt" inline="false"/></para>
